HEADWORD: capitalism
<hw>cap"i*tal*is`m</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧p"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧z`m)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>An economic system based on predominantly private
(individual or corporate) investment in and ownership of the means of
production, distribution, and exchange of goods and wealth; contrasted
with <contr>socialism</contr> or especially <contr>communism</contr>, in
which the state has the predominant role in the economy.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> capitalist economy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capitalist</ent>⟦br⟧
